# Frontend Style Rules

## Component And State Style

- Keep components focused; extract subcomponents when render logic grows.
- Co-locate component tests and related styles where project conventions allow.
- Minimize prop drilling with appropriate composition/context patterns.

## Rendering And Performance

- Avoid unnecessary re-renders by stabilizing derived state and handlers.
- Use list virtualization or pagination for large datasets.
- Defer non-critical work and optimize only after measurement.

## Forms And Validation

- Keep form validation rules explicit and consistent.
- Show actionable validation messages close to the affected field.
- Prevent duplicate submissions for long-running requests.

## Resilience And Maintainability

- Prefer explicit state transitions over implicit side effects.
- Keep side effects isolated and cancelable where applicable.
- Remove dead UI branches and unused style artifacts in touched areas.
